a regular school, we have here
as well.

23:49.428 --> 23:54.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: One state that
is doing
better is Massachusetts by
matching standards

23:54.199 --> 23:59.138 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
inside detention with what
students would
receive on the outside, tracking
students'

23:59.171 --> 24:04.710 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
progress through the system, and
helping kids
return to the community.

24:04.743 --> 24:09.515 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LYNNE ALLEN: Welcome to Judge
Connelly.

24:09.548 --> 24:14.820 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Lynne Allen runs the Judge John
Connelly detention
facility in Boston, the state's
most restrictive.

24:14.853 --> 24:20.426 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
