want to take,
so that they can go down a
positive road,

27:36.455 --> 27:39.458 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
so that they're not labeled and
defined by
whatever their charge is.

27:39.491 --> 27:44.863 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Finally,
managing the transition
from lockup to a secure facility
like Connelly

27:44.897 --> 27:49.868 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and eventually back to the
community often
through halfway houses like this
one is crucial,

27:49.902 --> 27:51.770 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
says commissioner Peter Forbes.

27:51.803 --> 27:53.572 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PETER FORBES, Commission,
Massachusetts Department
of Youth Services: Because, if
we have kids

27:53.605 --> 27:58.343 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
