understandings
about the largest planet in our
system and

29:49.888 --> 29:51.323 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the solar system itself.

29:51.356 --> 29:55.894 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That is the focus of our weekly
segment on
the Leading Edge of science.

29:55.927 --> 29:57.696 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
William Brangham takes it from
there.

29:57.729 --> 30:02.134 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The holiday
weekend is often
a time for big blockbuster
movies, and it's

30:02.167 --> 30:05.637 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
safe to say that concept has not
been lost
on NASA.

30:05.671 --> 30:09.441 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The space agency has just
released a kind
of movie trailer about what it
hopes will

30:09.474 --> 30:13.945 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
