than any spacecraft
has before, is supposed to reach
its destination.

30:19.685 --> 30:22.220 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But getting to Jupiter comes
with its own
risks.

30:22.254 --> 30:24.823 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This is how NASA describes it in
the trailer.

30:24.856 --> 30:36.535 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: It's a monster. It's
unforgiving. It's
relentless. It's spinning around
so fast its

30:36.568 --> 30:43.408 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
gravity is like a giant
slingshot, slinging
rocks, dust, electrons, whole
comets. Anything

30:43.442 --> 30:47.045 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
